TITLE: Indian, Chinese soldiers clash in disputed border region, injuries reported on both sides
SUMMARY: Indian and Chinese troops were involved in a violent clash in a disputed border region on Friday that reportedly resulted in several injuries on both sides.

TITLE: Ken DeLand disappearance in France shines light on Europe's 'abolished' borders travel zone
SUMMARY: The disappearance of Ken DeLand while studying abroad in France has pointed to Europe's Schengen zone where travelers aren't required to present passports, identification.

TITLE: Russia struggling to replenish arms even with Iran, North Korea aid: senior military official
SUMMARY: Russian arms stocks have dropped to the extend that it will 'struggle to replenish' its reserves even with support from nations like Iran and North Korea a senior military official said.

TITLE: Brother of American journalist Grant Wahl says 'I no longer suspect foul play' in death at World Cup
SUMMARY: Eric Wahl, brother of deceased American soccer journalist Grant Wahl, walked back speculation of foul play after Grant's body was returned to the U.S. from Qatar.

TITLE: Vehicle veers off mountain road in Nepal, leaving 12 dead
SUMMARY: A vehicle veered off a mountain road in Nepal that resulted in 12 dead. The passengers were coming from a wedding and rolled 650 feet down the mountain slope.

TITLE: Ken DeLand: American college student missing in France had trouble making friends, may have left voluntarily
SUMMARY: Ken DeLand, the American college student who went missing while studying abroad in France, had trouble making friends and may have voluntarily left, a French prosecutor said.

TITLE: Taiwan monitoring Chinese military planes, ships near island; deploys aircraft, vessels to respond
SUMMARY: Taiwan is it was monitoring a situation in which Chinese military planes and ships were near the island

TITLE: Afghanistan's Taliban displays pallets of cash received for 'humanitarian aid'
SUMMARY: The Taliban-controlled back of Afghanistan said last week it had received $40 million in cash.

TITLE: Ken DeLand, American college student missing in France, interned for New York senator: 'A positive energy'
SUMMARY: Ken DeLand, an American college student missing while on study abroad in France, previously interned for Republican New York state Sen. Pam Helming from 2019 to 2020.

TITLE: Dogs gifted by North Korean leader Kim Jong Un end up in South Korean zoo
SUMMARY: Kim Jung Un gave a pair of dogs to South Korea's former President, Moon Jae-in, in 2018. The country's new president gave them up, and they are now being sent to a zoo in the country.
